Abstract

Introduction back to ToC

The CityExplorer ontology is a comprehensive semantic framework designed to model and represent various aspects of tourism. This ontology aims to facilitate the integration, analysis, and exploration of data related to tourism cities.

CityExplorer :ce: Description back to ToC

This ontology models personalized tourist experiences by representing cities, points of interest, events, accommodations, restaurants, transportation, and their relationships.

AndalusianRestaurantc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: https://github.com/abolanceUOC/CityExplorer#AndalusianRestaurant

Refers to restaurants serving food from Andalusia
is equivalent to
Restaurant c and (hasCategory op value Andalusian ni)
has super-classes
RestaurantCategory c
is disjoint with
ItalianRestaurant c, JapaneseRestaurant c, MediterraneanHotel c, MexicanRestaurant c

SWRL rules

  • BeachCities
  • CulturalCities
  • RecommendedRestaurants

BeachCitiesback to ToC or SWRL ToC

rule for Cities with beach

City c(?c) , isCityOf op(?c,?a) , Attraction c(?a) , BeachAttraction c(?a) -> BeachCities c(?c)

CulturalCitiesback to ToC or SWRL ToC

Rule for Cities with cultural attractions or events

City c(?c) , isCityOf op(?c,?e) , Event c(?e) , CulturalEvent c(?e) , isCityOf op(?c,?a) , Attraction c(?a) , CulturalAttraction c(?a) -> CulturalCities c(?c)

RecommendedRestaurantsback to ToC or SWRL ToC

Rule for recommended restaurants aggregate rating greater than 4.0 and price range less or equal than 20.

Restaurant c(?r) , aggregateRating dp(?r,?ar) , priceRange dp(?r,?pr) , greaterThan(?) , lessThanOrEqual(?) -> RecommendedRestaurants c(?r)
